  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Combating Desertification through Education</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Under UNESCO&apos;s Man and the Biosphere (MAB) programme, the project will develop education and public awareness materials building on UNESCO&apos;s experience with initiatives such as Sandwatch and its MAST (Monitoring, Analysing, Sharing, Taking Action) approach, as well as MAB&apos;s Education Kit on Combating Desertification. The project will also explore the linkages between vocational training and local green economies. Starting from Elion Foundation&apos;s desertification project site in Kubuqi (Inner Mongolia, China), the project forges linkages to other areas in the region subject to desertification - including biosphere reserves in countries like Mongolia and the Central Asian subregion.</narrative>
  </description>
